"title": "2327: Jesus Christ, as servant",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2327: jesus christ, as servant",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ laid aside his majesty in order to serve humanity. His death is the supreme example of his servanthood: the fulfilling of the will of God his Father.</p>\n<h2>The prophets speak of the Messiah as a servant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:17-Matt12:21\">MAT 12:17–12:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1-Isa42:4\">ISA 42:1–42:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:1-Isa49:7\">ISA 49:1–49:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:4-Isa50:9\">ISA 50:4–50:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:13-Isa53:12\">ISA 52:13–53:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23-Ezek34:24\">EZK 34:23–34:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:24-Ezek37:25\">EZK 37:24–37:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:8\">ZEC 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ describes himself as a servant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:27\">LUK 22:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ acts as a servant</h2>\n<h3>By coming to dwell among humanity as a man</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6-Phil2:7\">PHP 2:6–2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a></p>\n<h3>By obeying God's will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:34\">JHN 4:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:30\">JHN 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:38\">JHN 6:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:31\">JHN 14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:5-Heb10:7\">HEB 10:5–10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:6-Ps40:8\">PSA 40:6–40:8</a></p>\n<h3>By ministering to his disciples</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:1-John13:17\">JHN 13:1–13:17</a></p>\n<h3>By dying on the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:8\">PHP 2:8</a></p>\n<h2>The exaltation of Jesus Christ the servant</h2>\n<h3>He will complete his task</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:4\">JHN 17:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:30\">JHN 19:30</a></p>\n<h3>He will be exalted by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:13\">ISA 52:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:26\">ACT 3:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's obedience and servanthood an example to believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:14-John13:15\">JHN 13:14–13:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5\">PHP 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21\">1PE 2:21</a></p>",
